# oepi-loepi water meter integration config.
#
# 1. Find the LAN IP of your Wemos D1 (the ESPEasy water sensor).
#    It also serves a page at  http://<ESP_IP>/water.html
# 2. Copy this file to:
#      /mnt/data/integrations/oepi-watermeter/oepi-watermeter.conf
# 3. Set ESP_IP below.
# 4. Restart the daemon:  pkill -f oepi-watermeter   (init respawns it)
#
# If ESP_IP is left at the placeholder, the daemon idles (does nothing)
# instead of hammering a non-existent host — so it's safe to install
# before you've wired up the meter.

ESP_IP=PUT_ESP_IP_HERE
